Objective 1: Develop and Launch the Website 

Specific: Create a fully functional and responsive website displaying detailed information about European music festivals. 

Measurable: The website will include profiles for at least 30 festivals, each containing key details such as name, location, genre, dates, costs, and booking information. 

Achievable: The development will use a modern web framework with a CMS to streamline data management. 

Relevant: This forms the foundation of artofest.comâ€™s core service and aligns with its goal to provide a central hub to discover festivals. 

Time-bound: To be completed by the 5th of May 2026. 

 

Objective 2: Ensure Responsive and User-Friendly Design 

Specific: Implement a responsive design that adapts to all major devices and screen sizes. 

Measurable: Website pages must load in under 4 seconds and maintain full functionality on desktop, tablet, and mobile devices. 

Achievable: Use of responsive front-end frameworks (e.g., React or Vue) and optimised images and code. 

Relevant: A smooth user experience is essential to encourage engagement and usability. 

Time-bound: Achieved by the Friday the 9th of January. 

 

Objective 3: Develop a Cross-Platform Mobile Application 

Specific: Create a mobile application for iOS and Android using the same codebase as the website. 

Measurable: The app will include all website features, such as festival browsing, search, and detailed festival profiles. 

Achievable: Implemented through a cross-platform framework (e.g., React Native or Flutter). 

Relevant: Extends platform accessibility to a wider audience. 

Time-bound: Completed by the 5th of May 2026. 

 

Objective 4: Integrate a Content Management System (CMS) 

Specific: Implement a CMS for administrators to manage and update festival data. 

Measurable: Admins should be able to add, edit, or remove festival entries without coding knowledge. 

Achievable: Use of an existing CMS solution (e.g., Strapi, WordPress Headless, or custom-built admin panel). 

Relevant: Ensures sustainability and scalability of the project post-launch. 

Time-bound: By the 5th of May 2026. 

 

Objective 5: Implement Future API Integrations 

Specific: Prepare the system for integration with third-party APIs for travel and accommodation. 

Measurable: Establish a test integration with at least one travel or hotel API. 

Achievable: Conducted in a later development phase once the main platform is stable. 

Relevant: Expands functionality and adds value for users planning festival trips. 

Time-bound: By the 5th of May 2026. 

 

Objective 6: Test, Deploy, and Evaluate Performance 

Specific: Test the website and app to ensure stability, security, and user satisfaction. 

Measurable: At least 90% of test users successfully navigating the platform without assistance. 

Achievable: Through systematic user testing and performance monitoring tools. 

Relevant: Ensures the platform is reliable and user-focused upon launch. 

Time-bound: By the 5th of May 2026. 
